article.headline: George Mason 56, Cleveland St. 47
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. (AP) -- Will Thomas and John Vaughan each scored 18 points and George Mason used smothering defense in the second half to beat Cleveland State 56-47 Tuesday night. George Mason (2-0) limited Cleveland State to just 36 percent shooting, including 27 percent in the second half. Cedric Jackson, who scored 11 first-half points, finished with 20 for the Vikings (1-1). Joe Davis added 13. The Patriots built a 48-40 lead with five minutes remaining and then held on in the final minutes by connecting on 8 of 10 free throws. Cleveland State trailed by eight early in the second half but pulled within one at 37-36 on Cedric Jackson's jumper with 11:12 remaining. Vlad Moldoveanu answered with a 3-pointer that fueled an 11-4 Patriots run in which they held Cleveland State to just one field goal over a seven-minute stretch. The Vikings led by as many as six in the first half by scoring in spurts and shooting 50 percent, including 4 of 5 from 3-point range. But George Mason took control with a 19-3 run and built a 31-28 halftime lead.
